**Risks / reviewer disagreement points:**
- Sort direction: ascending (oldest-first narration) vs descending (newest-first, like a log tail). Chose ascending for a forward-reading narrative; a reviewer may prefer newest-first or a `--reverse` flag. Defensible either way — documented and tiebroken deterministically.
- Gate attempts excluded as a first-class kind. A reviewer may argue gate Timestamps should appear as their own rows. Grounded rebuttal: no gate ref namespace exists; surfacing gate count in the run Summary preserves legibility without inventing storage or a second sort axis. Deferral is stated in docs.
- evals namespace (refs/etude/evals/*) is NOT included — the bead scopes the narration to runs + retros + (derived) gates. Note this explicitly; adding evals later is additive.
- Whether to fail-fast on a single malformed manifest vs skip-and-warn. Chose fail-fast to match run list/retro list exactly (consistency over partial output).

